Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 101a, 29. From same die as BM 1853,0326.11. Name Kallikrates
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1101)
